article.description: UCSB's ability to defend the perimeter led the Gauchos to a 71-62 victory over Xavier.
article.headline: Defense sends Gauchos to date with Texas Tech
article.linkText: UC Santa Barbara extends perimeter to beat Xavier
article.story:
LUBBOCK, Texas (AP) -- California-Santa Barbara's ability to defend the
perimeter attack of Xavier led the Gauchos to a 71-62
victory Sunday night and a place in the second round of the NCAA.

	   ''We did a good job of defending the 3's,'' Gaucho coach Mark
French said. ''I thought we were able to keep good pressure on the
ball and stay right with their guards.''

	   Mia Fisher scored 14 points for UC Santa Barbara in the
first-round Midwest Regional game.

	   The Gauchos (27-4) never trailed in building a 12-point lead in
the first half. Then they watched as a feisty 10th-seeded Xavier
team closed to one early in the second period at 33-32 on a
layup by Amy Waugh.

	   The two teams later exchanged 6-0 runs, giving the Gauchos a
53-43 lead with 8:43 remaining.

	   ''They had a great game plan,'' Waugh said. ''It was tough to
get a shot, and it was tough at times to take the ball all the way
to the hole.''

	   The Musketeers (20-10) trimmed the margin to six points at 68-62
with 31.9 seconds remaining on a free throw by Waugh. But a free
throw by Kristen Mann and two by Debby Caine sealed the game for
the Gauchos.

	   ''I think early they did a good job of getting pressure on us,
but as we got into the flow of the game we were able to get a lot
of good looks at the basket,'' Xavier coach Kevin McGuff said.
''The ball just didn't go in for us tonight.''

	   UC Santa Barbara advances to face second-seeded Texas Tech on
Tuesday night in the second round.

	   Lindsay Taylor scored 13 points, and Mann and Jess Hansen added
12 each for seventh-seeded UC Santa Barbara, which lead 33-27 at
halftime.

	   The Gauchos led 32-20 with 3:55 left in the first half before
the Musketeers closed the margin to six on a 7-1 run.

	   Waugh scored 19 points, and Tara Boothe added 16 and pulled down
12 rebounds for the Musketeers.
